docs/effect-v4-migration.md:1:# Backend Effect v4 Migration Notes
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:3:Relay now targets `effect@4.0.0-beta.65`, the Effect v4 package published from the effect-smol repository.
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:5:The first migration pass keeps existing IPC-facing Promise APIs intact and moves backend internals onto a small Effect runtime adapter in `src/main/services/effectRuntime.ts`. The adapter provides:
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:7:- `runBackendEffect` for running backend Effect programs at existing Promise boundaries.
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:9:- `fromPromise` and `fromSync` helpers that preserve existing thrown/rejected error values while routing async work through Effect v4.
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:11:Codex backend entry points keep their public Promise signatures, but test and production dependencies are adapted into Effect layers at the boundary:
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:23:- Public backend function signatures remain source-compatible while their implementation uses Effect at the runtime boundary.
docs/effect-v4-migration.md:24:- Codex run cancellation still uses the SDK `AbortSignal`; active run cleanup is verified after abort and stream-start failure paths.
